            "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
            "body": "> I came to the conclusion that disabling the GC is an unsolvable multi-threading disaster.\n\nYeah good point. I know it was added for a reason in cupy, but it did seem strange and something that would be nice to remove. But I had not realized how bad it is (I suppose it might work in simple enough functions if you hold the GIL, but then free-threading will be an issue anyway... reminds me of the attempt disastrous attempt to handle signals in NumPy).\n\nSorry, coming from recursive-mutex I had missed the [free-threading docs](https://docs.cython.org/en/stable/src/userguide/freethreading.html) explaining that you already have much of this for critical section and `pymutex`.\nThat may or may not help with what I have (I suspect the recurisve-mutex may not be needed, but I am not sure yet).  But... while it may be nice to make C++ constructs better it seems the burning needs around free-threading may be making the hidden stuff safer rather than new language constructs.",
