            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "I didn't have too many other thoughts beyond what I originally posted on this so haven't followed up as promised.\n\nYour\n\n```\n# Note that the condition is the wrong way round in your code!\n# Hopefully it's just a quick example and not copied from somewhere real\nif lock.try_lock():\n    with nogil:\n        lock.lock()\n```\n\ndefinitely should be covered by the new `py_safe` functions I've added. Using them with `unique_lock` rather than `scoped_lock` means you can release it without needing the whole function. Although obvious it's not as nice as a `with` statement.\n\nThey should be in the next Cython release (hopefully soon) so feedback is welcome on how usable they are.",
